{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c7765bc9-7f27-45fd-9617-b1fe8775456b","content":"The working directory appears empty, so I'll answer from general knowledge.\n\nFor a **Web API project**, the common templates are:\n\n| Template | Command |\n|----------|---------|\n| ASP.NET Core Web API | `dotnet new webapi` |\n| Minimal API | `dotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis` |\n| Web API with controllers | `dotnet new webapi --use-controllers` |\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD (org) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --name MyApi\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer or cookie auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` or integrate with Identity. Run `dotnet new webapi --help` for full options.\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a project with a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0209df46-8e6f-472a-864c-3cdc8a439c41","outputTokens":273,"requestId":"5022:1025EC:312DF83:35BAF05:69FBE1E4"},"id":"2303bf32-2f9e-41c5-8b43-cee79a808371","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:50:51.370Z","parentId":"41064feb-0dea-4f03-96a2-81dcc65dd76d"}
